        "title": "France, Spain, England and Argentina enter FIFA World Cup semi-finals",
        "summary": "The semi-final line-up for the FIFA World Cup has been confirmed following the conclusion of the quarter-final matches. In the first semi-final, France will take on Spain on Wednesday. The match will begin at 12:30 a.m. Indian Standard Time. France reached the last four after defeating Morocco 2-0 in the quarter-finals, while Spain advanced with […]",
        "article": "The semi-final line-up for the FIFA World Cup has been confirmed following the conclusion of the quarter-final matches. In the first semi-final, France will take on Spain on Wednesday. The match will begin at 12:30 a.m. Indian Standard Time. France reached the last four after defeating Morocco 2-0 in the quarter-finals, while Spain advanced with a 2-1 victory over Belgium. The second semi-final will be played between England and Argentina on Thursday at 12:30 a.m. Indian Standard Time. England secured their place in the semi-finals with a 2-1 extra-time win over Norway, while Argentina defeated Switzerland 3-1 in the quarter-finals. The winners of the two semi-finals will meet in the FIFA World Cup final on the 20th of July at New Jersey Stadium. The losing teams will contest the third-place play-off on the 19th of July in Miami.",
